<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Martin Gruenberg, chairman of the Federal Depo=
sit Insurance Corp., has helped sell a lot of banks in his time. =E2=80=A6 =
But SVB was different. A vast amount of its customer deposits fell outside =
the FDIC=E2=80=99s guarantee cap of $250,000, so finding a buyer =E2=80=94 =
almost certainly another bank =E2=80=94 to take on the giant liability was =
a tough sell. Any sweetener, like an agreement with the FDIC to help should=
er future losses, would risk leaving the agency on the hook for more than i=
ts share. The FDIC=E2=80=99s own rules force it to seek the least costly ou=
tcome for itself, and in this case, that was potentially to let SVB fail an=
d pay out the insured losses only, regardless of the broader consequences. =
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s the point Gruenberg stressed in=
 frantic meetings last weekend at FDIC=E2=80=99s headquarters and on the ph=
one with top officials from the Federal Reserve and the Treasury Department=
, the people with knowledge of the matter said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The only way to sidestep the obligation to pro=
tect the FDIC=E2=80=99s funds, Gruenberg said, was for the government to sa=
y that SVB presented a systemic risk to the US economy. That extraordinary =
step would mean the FDIC=E2=80=99s pot could be used to pay out uninsured l=
osses, with banks that pay into the fund as a regulatory obligation eventua=
lly covering the excess costs.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the time government officials agreed that=
=E2=80=99s what needed to happen =E2=80=94 well into Sunday =E2=80=94 the w=
indow to find a buyer was closing fast.=C2=A0=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, even once an auction started, officials=
 were reluctant to let the biggest US banks make a bid. A bank like JPMorga=
n risked exceeding limits on its deposit base, and regulators weren=E2=80=
=99t willing to waive the rules to let them in.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What was left on the table wasn=E2=80=99t nece=
ssarily a compelling prospect. To some of the people close to the negotiati=
ons, it felt like Gruenberg had only agreed to an auction to prove just how=
 uninterested the US banking industry was.</p>
</blockquote>
